modules.description: This module provides functions to access predefined color schemes from libraries like ColorBrewer, Office, and Tableau, focusing on sequential, diverging, and categorical palettes with 3–12 color steps. It works with JavaScript objects (`Js.t`) wrapping `Scheme.t` values to define color gradients in Chart.js visualizations, supporting use cases like accessibility (e.g., colorblind-friendly palettes), thematic consistency (Office/Corporate styling), and data-driven aesthetics (e.g., diverging scales for heatmaps). The bindings enable OCaml developers to integrate these curated palettes into JavaScript charting workflows via `Js_of_ocaml`.

This module manages color scheme configurations for Chart.js visualizations, offering functions to create, retrieve, and apply color palettes globally or within specific chart options. It operates on `colorschemes` JavaScript objects, enabling use cases such as applying ColorBrewer palettes to bar charts or setting corporate-themed gradients in line charts. Key operations include setting up default configurations, integrating with chart options, and applying schemes across all visualizations.
